<subSubSection id="BCF1654AFFE0FFB8FDBCF987AEABF8A6" pageId="6" pageNumber="98" type="description">
<paragraph id="F45436C1FFE0FFB8FDBCF987A937F932" blockId="6.[136,1452,1540,2035]" pageId="6" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFE0FFB8FDBCF987AC7DF9DB" bold="true" box="[136,284,1540,1566]" pageId="6" pageNumber="98">Description:</emphasis>
Caespitose plants; stems (25)40–100(300) cm; nodes in the culm glabrous. Leaf-blades 
<quantity id="33139B24FFE0FFB8F9DEF987A839F9DA" box="[1258,1368,1540,1567]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="98" unit="cm" value="35.0" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="15.0">15–55 cm</quantity>
× 
<quantity id="33139B24FFE0FFB8F847F987ADD7F986" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="5.0">5–12 mm</quantity>
, flat, deeply ridged, scabrous adaxially and glabrous abaxially. Panicle (5)7–20(25) × 
<quantity id="33139B24FFE0FFB8F94DF9ABA985F986" box="[1145,1252,1576,1603]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="98" unit="cm" value="2.85" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="0.7">0.7–5 cm</quantity>
, open, lanceolate, without spikelets in the lower third. Pedicels shorter than the spikelets, pubescent. Spikelets 
<quantity id="33139B24FFE0FFB8F98FF9CFA821F9A2" box="[1211,1344,1612,1639]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.025" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.65" pageId="6" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="10.25" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="6.5">6.5–14 mm</quantity>
, cuneate. Glumes lanceolate. Glumes longer than the spikelet. Lower glume 
<quantity id="33139B24FFE0FFB8FEB8F9F3AE9DF94E" box="[908,1020,1648,1675]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="5.0">5–12 mm</quantity>
, 1-veined; upper glume 
<quantity id="33139B24FFE0FFB8F822F9F2A8E7F94E" box="[1302,1414,1649,1675]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="14.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="4.0">4–14 mm</quantity>
, 3- veined. Lemma of male florets 
<quantity id="33139B24FFE0FFB8FCC3F917AF1CF96A" box="[503,637,1684,1711]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.75" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="7.75" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.5">5.5–10 mm</quantity>
, elliptic or oblong, membranaceous, scaberulous, ciliolate on margins, obtuse. Awn 2-6-mm, subapically inserted. Lemma of apical female floret membranaceous, glabrous in the lower part and scabrous in the upper part. Muticous or awned, but awn always shorter than 
<quantity id="33139B24FFE0FFB8F93AF95EA933F932" box="[1038,1106,1757,1783]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="98" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F45436C1FFE0FFB8FD89F883AC35F8FA" blockId="6.[136,1452,1540,2035]" pageId="6" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="C69FEAD3FFE0FFB8FD89F883AC10F8DE" bold="true" box="[189,369,1792,1819]" pageId="6" pageNumber="98">Leaf anatomy:</emphasis>
Stomata 20–50 μm, in the adaxial surface. Hooks present. Leaf section closed with 20–40 quadrangular ribs.
</paragraph>
